line_1: To bring me here an headless trunk?
line_2: Z—ds! cries the Doctor, are you drunk,
Sapless Limbs all bent, and shrunk,

line_1: To buy a new coat, and to line an old trunk:
line_2: From scribbling for hire, when my credit is sunk,

line_1: When wrinkling with a sneer his trunk,
line_2: Friend, quoth the Elephant, you're drunk;
